Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Remove the @Slow Cooked British Pork{425%g} from the packaging. Place in an #ovenproof dish{} along with the juices and cover loosely with #foil{}.

Roast on the middle shelf, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pop the @Mixed Peppers and Red Onion{1%pack} onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Roast on the top shelf, ~{20-25%minutes}.

When ready, remove the pork from the oven, reserve 1 tbsp of juices per person, then discard the foil and any remaining juices. Use two #forks{} to shred the pork. IMPORTANT: Ensure the pork is piping hot throughout.

Stir in the @Gochujang Paste{50%g} and @Honey{15%g}. Season with salt and pepper.

Warm the @Plain Taco Tortillas{6} in the oven, ~{1-2%minutes}. Share between your plates.

Spread the @Mayonnaise{64%g} over each tortilla. Top with the roasted veg and gochujang pork.

Crumble over the @Feta Cheese{100%g}. Sprinkle over the @Crispy Onions{1%sachet} to finish.

Enjoy!